			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">As far as I can tell, it reads both chips at once but can write to only one of them. It chooses whether to write to the even chip or the odd chip based on bit 0 of the B bus. Bit 0 is clear during $2118 access and set during $2119 access. Does this 16-bit memory support 68000-style writes to only the bottom half or top half of a 16-bit word?<br /><br />A 16-bit memory would break background rendering in mode 7, as it relies on driving separate addresses to the even and odd chips.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

