					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">⇦ ⇩ ⇧ ⇨<br />Let's play some <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Double_data_rate" class="postlink">DDR</a>.<br /><br />Whether one 8-bit RAM can do the job of two depends on how fast the RAM is and how fast the PPU expects it to be. Look at the 8-bit VRAM in the Genesis for example: the VDP makes two 8-bit accesses to the same chip per pixel, compared to the S-PPU's one 8-bit access to each chip per pixel.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

